# RC Circuit — Schematic View

A companion to the `rc-circuit.tbk` plot-based view. Here we show the actual
**schematic** — a 9 V battery, a 1 kΩ resistor, and a 1 mF capacitor in
series. When the loop closes, current flows, the resistor drops voltage,
and charge accumulates on the capacitor until it equals the battery EMF.

$$
V_0 = i R + V_C, \qquad V_C(t) = V_0 \left(1 - e^{-t/\tau}\right),
\qquad \tau = RC = 1\ \text{s}
$$

At each step we highlight the element whose state is dominant in that
moment.

```text
1. Switch closes. Capacitor is empty, voltage drop across R is maximum.
2. Current decays as capacitor charges.
3. V_C rises toward V0 = 9 V.
4. After ~5τ, circuit is effectively at steady state.
```

